article.headline: Virginia Military 156, VA Intermont 95
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Reggie Williams scored 45 points and VMI broke 24 school and individual records Wednesday night in a 156-95 win over Virginia Intermont of the NAIA. The Keydets (2-2) scored 74 points off 48 Virginia Intermont turnovers, including 35 steals. VMI made 60 field goals -- the most ever at the school and in Cameron Hall -- and sank 21 3-pointers, another school and arena record. Williams' 45 points set a new individual record at the school and Cameron Hall, as did his 18 field goals. The team also broke the record for the most points scored and the biggest margin of victory. Chavis Holmes had 31 points for the Keydets, Travis Holmes had 26 and Matt Murrer added 22. Juan Ornelas led the Cobras (1-4) with 21.
